er intelligence officers afio he is married with two children from a previous marriage and resides in mclean virginia his hobbies include collecting art especially primitive american art intelligence careeredit pavitt served in the united states army from  as an intelligence officer and was a legislative assistant with the house of representatives from  until  pavitt joined the cia in  as a career trainee with postings to europe asia and washingtoncitation needed he was posted to vienna  east berlin  budapest hungary and malaysia  he was expelled pngd from east germany he was chief of station in luxembourg  he served as a branch chief in the africa division from  to  he served on the national security council team under brent scowcroft as senior intelligence advisor to president george hw bush after being assigned to work across the agency operationalanalytical divide in the directorate of intelligence he became the founder and first chief of the directorate of operations counterproliferation division cpd gordon oehler then chief of the directorate of intelligences nonproliferation center criticized this as being redundant and stepping on his turf this was considered a specious critique by veteran agency humint operations officers however especially those who had been assigned under oehler previously and realized that oehler held humint counterproliferation operations—indeed covert operations in general—in considerable disdain pavitt hand picked operations officers some of which were nonofficial cover officers nocs including valerie plame to staff the cpd in  he was appointed associate deputy director of operations he was deputy director of operations from  until his resignation in  in  the cpd took down the nuclear black market being operated by abdul qadeer khan after september   pavitt was responsible for sending special activities division teams to afghanistan pakistan indonesia thailand and somalia to capture al qaeda members the first hellfire missiles fired from drones were under his command they were aimed at an al qaeda convoy in sudan in which all occupants including an american citizen were killed in april  he appeared before the  commission the bbc called his  commission appearance unprecedented the commissions report said that shortly after bushs election pavitt told the presidentelect that osama bin laden was one of the gravest threats to the country he also added that killing the al qaeda leader would have an effect but not stop the threat posed by the terrorist organization when bush put porter goss in charge of the agency pavitt reportedly opposed the internal reorganizations announced by goss on the ground that they might do damage to a strategic effort that has produced excellent work on terrorism and a variety of other important issues on june   he unexpectedly announced his retirement one day after george tenet the cia says pavitts decision was unconnected with tenets departurecitation needed pavitt was succeeded by his deputy stephen kappes on june   pavitt delivered one of his last speeches as ddo to the foreign policy association pavitt is a recipient of the cias distinguished intelligence medal he is also a recipient of the cia distinguished career intelligence medal the cia director’s medal and the donovan award postcia workedit he is an advisor to the patriot defense group llc a defense and intelligence contracting company that directly supports the training requirements of the defense and intelligence communities to olton solutions ltd in the united kingdom and to the scowcroft group he is a director of caci international inc criticism and controversyedit some former operations officers are critical of pavitt citing  international postings over  years in a year career as insufficient experience for a deputy director of operations the senate intelligence committee report on cia torture found that pavitt was told that rectal exams of at least two cia prisoners had been conducted with excessive force but he took action to stop this behavior external linksedit appointment of james l pavitt as special assistant to the president for national security affairs june   transcript wednesdays  commission hearings the washington post march   in photos counterterrorism officials testify on it challenges  dan verton of computerworld april   press release cia deputy director for operations announces retirement odci mclean va june   exspy master praises cias effectiveness mu graduate advises caution in revamping  josh flory of columbia daily tribune october   excia official defends detention policies  dana priest of the washington post october   page a retired official defends the cias performance  dana priest of the washington post november   page a goss pushes change at cia  bill gertz of the washington times november   james l pavitts resume the scowcroft group james pavitt the center for torture accountability archived from the original on  retrieved   speechesedit address to duke university law school conference jim pavitt deputy director for operations april   remarks of deputy director of operations james l pavitt on the th anniversary of the office of strategic services cias predecessor june   remarks by the deputy director for operations james l pavitt at the american bar association standing committee on law and national security breakfast program january   posted written statement for the record of james l pavitt deputy director for operations before the national commission on terrorist attacks upon the united states april   remarks by deputy director for operations james l pavitt foreign policy association june   americas clandestine service foreign policy association june   referencesedit  a b c d dana priest retired official defends the cias performance  washington post november    a b c d james l pavitt bio  scowcroft group  a b c vernon loeb rebuilding clandestine operations  washington post september    a b jason vest spy versus spy  the american prospect june