defense group llc snapshotpeople  overviewboard memberscommittees executive profile james l pavitt strategic advisor patriot defense group llcagetotal calculated compensationthis person is connected to  board members in  different organizations across  different industriessee board relationships background mr james l pavitt serves as a strategic advisor at patriot defense group llc mr pavitt is a principal of scowcroft group he is a coowner and president of jlp associates he was an executive partner at torch hill investment partners llc specializing in intelligence he provides strategic advice and risk assessments to clients in the fields of homeland security counterterrorism financial services defense and information technology at scowcroft group he has  more than  years of experience in the intelligence community with proven expertise in homeland security counterterrorism financial services defense and information technology given his career mr pavitt is a nationally recognized expert of intelligence and counterterrorism he retired as deputy director for operations of cia for operations after five years in that position he managed the agencys globally deployed personnel and nearly half of its multibillion dollar budget he also served as the head of americas clandestine service leading the cias operational response to the attacks of september   as chief of the cias counterproliferation division he managed and directed intelligence operations against global proliferation networks mr pavitt was a career cia officer with the clandestine service and served as special assistant to the president on the national security council staff responsible for intelligence matters from  to  he served as senior intelligence advisor on the national security council team for president george hw bush early in his career he served as a legislative assistant in the us house of representatives he has been an outside director of caci international inc since august   he serves as member of advisory board of olton solutions ltd he also serves on the board of directors of the patriot defense group llc he served as a director of advanced blast protection since august   and cub energy inc from may   to june  mr pavitt is a recipient of the cias distinguished intelligence medal for his superior work in these capacities he received a ba in history from the university of missouri and was a national defense education act fellow at clark universityread full background corporate headquarters  southhall lanemaitland florida united statesphone fax  board members memberships presentoutside directorcaci international inc education ba university of missouricolumbia other affiliations caci international incuniversity of missouricolumbiatorch hill investment partners llcadvanced blast protection inccub energy inc annual compensation there is no annual compensation data available stocks options there is no stock options data available total compensation there is no total compensation data available request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquiries please contact sp global market intelligence directly by clicking here stock quotes market data is delayed at least  minutes company lookup competitor compensationthere is no competitor compensation data available sponsored financial commentaries sponsored links browse companies a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z              request profile update only a company representative may request an update for the company profile documentation will be required to contact patriot defense group llc please visit  company data is provided by sp global market intelligence please use this form to report any data issues information missing  please enter your information in the following fields company name your name your email address your phone number 